I have never been so disappointed. My first visit into this Cosi, I ordered their newly advertised Chicken Avocodo bowl and I got the WORST food posioning I've EVER had. I was sick for three days, and the doctor confirmed it was due to their under prepared chicken.  This morning I went in to a Cosi to get a bagel, and after waiting 15 minutes for the slow staff, I get back to my office with the WRONG order, HAIR in my bagle and a very sharp piece of plastic (not sure where it's from? the container?...) in my cream cheese.  NEVER EVER go here. I'm planning to march back there this morning and file a formal complaint with the manager.

When you need receipts for reimbursement this is unacceptable. If u cant give receipts be upfront and i will go somewhere that can. Or get off your butt and put paper in the machine.

I do NOT recommend this Cosi restaurant.  I've been here more than once (3 times) hoping that my past experiences were just bad luck, but the service is just POOR.  The food is okay, not spectacular. You can do better at Corner Bakery or Au Bon Pain for the same type fare.  At lunch time; the lines are usually very long. On one visit in particular, I came in for breakfast when it was empty and one other customer and I had to wait several minutes for someone just to take our order and money.  I think check-out setup is awkward.  You order in one line; wait in a second to pay for food and low and behold, your food STILL isn't ready.  On visit #2 they gave me the wrong order and then I had to wait AGAIN for them to start from scratch.  So much for a quick to go order  On the third visit, I only ordered a green tea smoothie (delicious!)  but high in price for the 8 ounces they gave me.  Again more waiting. What's worse is that you can't even call ahead because they don't answer the phone.  Too bad...I work right across the street, but this obviously is NOT a match made in heaven.  I give up on this place forever.  Save time and just pick another lunch spot.  I'm not a hater, but I'm also not a waiter.
